{
  "stem": "2718.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And also, malnutrition, lack of medication, because nobody in his right mind went to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It's called the Lazarette.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Anybody who went to the hospital was really desperate.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he got an infection, but it was from the bags of cement, from the cement itself.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were all-- after a while we bandaged our fingers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] But it was rather, rather risky sort of thing to bandage your fingers to protect yourself, because if you slipped the bag and the bag fell, and it busted open, they just-- you know, it wasn't so pleasant, what, what, what came afterwards.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he, he developed eczemas and there was-- there was no other way.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was no other way except to, to take him to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There's no way.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Had he lost a lot of weight by now?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, probably 30, 35.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sorry?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, my father was 48 when he died.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a-- he was a very tall man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he looked-- he looked much skinnier than, than I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I wasn't [INAUDIBLE] skinny.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Somehow a young person has got more resilience than an older person, and I-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] somehow I kept my strength, except my fingers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was in a much better condition.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we had-- we had a doctor in the barrack, Dr.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Lieberman, who was right opposite on the-- on the opposite bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he, he he kept-- he kept bringing us medications.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he tried to look after us with whatever he had he gave us, but it wasn't to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
